  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>red&nbsp;</strong><strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong> over a medium-high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced&nbsp;onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 or until soft and starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>mini cooking</strong>&nbsp;<strong>chorizo</strong> roughly into small pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;chopped chorizo</strong> to the <strong>onions</strong> and cook them both for a further 2-3 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the&nbsp;<strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chipotle paste</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> - this is your <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>spicy tomato stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the liquid reduces to form a loose paste</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate the <strong>cheddar&nbsp;</strong><strong>cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely, discarding the root end<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>tortillas</strong> to a large baking tray</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>tomato chorizo mixture</strong> between the tortillas and spread it out towards the edges</p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle each tortilla with the<strong>&nbsp;grated cheese</strong> and <strong>sliced&nbsp;</strong><strong>spring onion- </strong>these are your <strong>tortizzas</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/693.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place the <strong>tortizzas</strong> into the oven and cook for 10 min or until the cheese has melted and the edges of the tortizzas are browned and starting to crisp</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, mix the <strong>pomegranate molasses</strong> with the<strong> mayonnaise</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> - this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
